Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.81,0:00:07.01,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Once again, we're wrapping up \Nat the very last second.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.73,0:00:09.88,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we made it in time, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.88,0:00:11.40,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.40,0:00:14.38,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,Not being able to record the voice-overs \Nmeans we didn't make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.38,0:00:15.96,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,True...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.96,0:00:18.03,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to do the dubbing live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.03,0:00:21.65,main,K,0000,0000,0000,,All thanks to a certain someone \Nand their late animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.10,0:00:24.56,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,I can go ahead and record the performance,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.56,0:00:26.83,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,but there's a lot of echo \Nin the auditorium...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.37,0:00:30.37,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if it'll be good \Nenough to use on the DVDs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.37,0:00:33.38,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still worried about how Onocchy's \Nreads are gonna turn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:34.97,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go ahead and run it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.87,0:01:01.61,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Asakusa?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.37,0:01:04.23,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't balanced it yet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.23,0:01:06.50,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Right. As it stands, only the timing is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.50,0:01:09.51,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Although I was making adjustments \Nwhile it was playing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.51,0:01:13.62,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,About the music in cut 6... \NDoes it seem out of sync to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.62,0:01:15.68,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because the action \Non screen doesn't happen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.68,0:01:17.66,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,until after the music peaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.66,0:01:19.01,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,We could try delaying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.66,0:01:21.58,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,You mean offsetting it even \Nmore from the action?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.58,0:01:23.35,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that mess with the big hit?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.35,0:01:24.39,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.94,0:01:31.91,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure why, but I think that's better!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.61,0:01:36.61,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The music is setting the tone before \Nthe action, and leading the audience along!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.61,0:01:40.17,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,There were a few spots where the music \Nand the action didn't have the right tone,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.17,0:01:43.14,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,where I was thinking we \Ncould use different tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.14,0:01:47.26,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,For cut 150 and 82...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.26,0:01:49.21,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,If we use the music from cut 24,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.21,0:01:51.12,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,we can create a motif linking \Nthe different scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.12,0:01:52.07,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.07,0:01:54.42,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like it might work. Let me try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.17,0:01:58.93,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,Something about the music for\N cut 86 doesn't sit right with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.18,0:02:04.39,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,What if we dropped \Nthe music for that part?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.10,0:02:08.19,main,D,0000,0000,0000,,You mean to put an emphasis \Non the sound effects from 79?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.19,0:02:14.94,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The animation is amazing for that part.\N So by subtracting the music...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.14,0:02:28.29,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,So cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.29,0:02:30.50,main,A,0000,0000,0000,,That makes the scene really stand out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.50,0:02:33.23,main,M,0000,0000,0000,,You're some kind of music master, Asakusa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:42.80,main,Staff,0000,0000,0000,,We are so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.80,0:02:45.14,main,Staff,0000,0000,0000,,Who would've thought production \Nwould end up canceled
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.14,0:02:48.98,main,Staff,0000,0000,0000,,because the director and screenwriter \Ntried to murder a producer?
